cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CC

The paper discusses the No Free Lunch theorems and algorithmic information theory in the context of supervised learning, which is a core topic in machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses information theory, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper proposes a new algorithm for classification, which is a sub-topic of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the efficacy of a heuristic, which is related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
